devdoc.details: Only one address can hold one SPACE token as the tokenID is a hash of the buyer's address

baseURI().details: Returns the base URI set via {_setBaseURI}. This will be automatically added as a prefix in {tokenURI} to each token's URI, or to the token ID if no specific URI is set for that token ID.

buy().details: Buy a unique token One address can only hold one token as the token ID is based on a hashed version of the buyer's address The price of the token is based on a bonding curve function

params.x: the x value in the bonding curve graph Assuming current bonding curve function of y = x^2 + basePrice

returns._0: price at the specific position in bonding curve

rent(uint256,string).details: Allows users to rent a SPACE token of choice

params.tokenId: ID of the token to check

sell(uint256).details: Sell a unique token Sell and burn the token that has been minted

params.tokenId: the ID of the token being sold - The price of the token is based on a bonding curve function - Will check if token is legitimate

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: See {IERC165-supportsInterface}.     * Time complexity O(1), guaranteed to always use less than 30 000 gas.

devdoc.title: Decentramall SPACE token

claim(uint256).notice: Owner can claim rent right on Day 1 of renting*
